choices.text: In research, it is tough to determine how good of a researcher you are. One way that people determine how good you are is by looking at your $H$-Index. Each paper has a certain number of citations. Your $H$-Index is the largest number $H$ such that you have $H$ papers with at least $H$ citations. Given the number of citations on each paper you have written, what is your $H$-Index
